  "title": "Cleaning up an island in Brazil that is a magnet for plastic waste | Nestia",
  "text": "Fisherman Jose Antonio Crispin recalls the days when he would throw out a net and get a decent haul of fish around Pombeba Island, a small oasis in Rio de Janeiro’s iconic Guanabara Bay that is being suffocated by trash.“Now, the net only brings garbage, garbage, garbage. And we can’t survive that way,” the 60-year-old said, as a team of volunteers including a two-time Olympic sailing champion endured record heat late February to collect hundreds of sacks of plastic waste in a clean-up drive on the island.",
